ategie markiert einen Paradigmenwechsel in der Entwicklungspolitik und stützt die These John W. Meyers einer sich verbreitenden universalistischen Weltkultur.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aArmut. 4aEntwicklungspolitik. 4aEntwicklungssoziologie. 4aGlobalisierung. 4aGrundsicherung. 4aPolitik. 4aSozialhilfe. 4aSoziologie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aGlobalization.  aPolitics.  aPoverty.  aSociology of Development.  aSociology.1 aBuhr, Petra, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTraiser-Diop, Ute, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut0 cprintz978389942460740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839404607?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839404607zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839404607/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA